/*
 *
 *
 *  Explanation and usefil tips!
 *
 * Position Fixed:
 *  - At the moment of generating the invoice, the generate-code will go through all the HTML. If this code runs into a "position: fixed", then this will only be used on the page it will be generated.
 *  - If you set fixed above the code, then this will be visible on each page. Because the code runs into this first. (first page).
 *  - If you set fixed on the bottom of a table/div/etc where there is a chance that there is a lot of content (Like the invoice row tabel) that will be generated on the second or higher page,
 *  - Then the position: fixed will be set from this page.
 *  - Example #1: html code on top, each page will show this piece of HTML (Usefull for header/footer)
 *  - Example #2: html code in the middle, on the moment of generating on the current page, it will be shown on the same page and all following pages. (For example header/footer, except on the first page)
 *  - Example #3L html code on the bottom, will only be shown on the last page because there are no following pages.
 *
 * Position Absolute:
 *  - The rules here are the same as position: fixed, but it will only by shown on 1 page (no repeat)
 *  - example #1: html code on top, will only be shown on page 1.
 *  - example #2: html code in the middel, on the moment the invoice will be generated, this will only be shown on the current page (!! this is being discouraged, because this can give unexpected results)
 *  - example #3: html code on the bottom, will only be shown on the last page
 *
 * Page numbering
 * - In the css above is a usefull class:
 * - .pagenum.before { content: counter(page); }
 * - Use for example <p class="pagenum"></p> in the HTML code to show a page number (will be automatically filled)
 *
 * Use cm in stead of px (pixels)!
 *
 * page-break-before, page-break-inside, page-break-after
 *  - Use this to let a piece of text not break on the next page with "page-break-inside: avoid".
 *  - Or to generate a new page at the <h1></h1> by using a "page-break-before: always;" an a h1 element.
 *  - More information:
 *  - - http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/pr_print_pagebb.asp
 * 	- - http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/pr_print_pagebi.asp
 *  - - http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/pr_print_pageba.asp
 *
 * <img>
 *  - Use base64 to add in-line images. URLS are not supported due to safety
 * 	- http://webcodertools.com/imagetobase64converter
 *  - <img src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAAN............../>
 *  - With the help of css you can resize the image
 *
 * <span class="totalpages"></span>
 *  - Show the total amount of pages.
 *  - Note: Because the code first counts how many pages there will be, and render after this. This is pretty intensive and takes twice as long. So we descourage the use of this code.
 *  - If you take this out of the HTML code, the calculation will not be executed.
 *
 * {{variabels}}
 *  - You will find all the variabels that can be used in the control panel. System -> Settings - System messages
 *  - If you want to use HTML in the text (for example in {{STR_FACTUUR_MACHTIGING}} ), put 3 {{{ ... }}} around it instead of 2 and the HTML will be generated.
 *  - Do you need more documentation? https://github.com/janl/mustache.js / http://mustache.github.io/
 *  - You can create a 'loop' (see invoice_lines)
 *  - An 'if' works the same,  see for example STR_FACTUUR_BETALINGSTERMIJN
 *
 */


</style>
